    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/police-body-camera-footage-alabama-restrictions">
                                    When Alabama Police Kill, Surviving Family Can Fight Years to See Bodycam Footage. There’s No Guarantee They Will.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Alabama is among the most restrictive states for disclosing body-camera footage when police kill loved ones. Surviving family members often must go to court to get access to the video, and even if successful, they usually can’t share it publicly.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/umar-farooq">Umar Farooq</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-12-28EST05:00">Dec. 28, 2023, 5 a.m. EST</time>
        </p>

            </div>
</div>
                    


        
                    
<div class="story-card story-card--standard">
    
    


                    
    
        <div class="lead-art">
            <a class="aspect-3-2" href="https://www.propublica.org/article/body-camera-videos-police-killings-remain-hidden-from-public">
                <img
                    alt=""
                    src="data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20xmlns%3D%27http%3A%2F%2Fwww.w3.org%2F2000%2Fsvg%27%20width%3D%273%27%20height%3D%272%27%20style%3D%27background%3Atransparent%27%2F%3E"
